// ============================================================  
// Readme of UIWorldGeneratorController  
// ============================================================  

// ============================================================  
// Description  
// ============================================================  

// This script serves as the primary interface controller for a procedural world generator.
// It links all UI elements (toggles, sliders, buttons, inputs) to the parameters of the internal BiomeGenerator.
// It handles real-time visual feedback, automatic world generation upon parameter changes, and manages dynamic statistical data output for the generated world.

// ============================================================  
// Responsibilities  
// ============================================================  

// - Synchronizes values between the visual UI elements and the internal BiomeGenerator.
// - Calculates and dynamically updates world statistics (enemy and entity counts per biome).
// - Manages an isolated "Auto Generate" system that listens for changes in UI elements.
// - Handles UI visual feedback, including hover states, color changes, alpha fades, and button rotation animations.
// - Casts a ray from the mouse to read and display exact tile and biome data via a hover legend.
// - Saves the original default state of the generator, allowing a complete "Reset to Default" action.

// ============================================================  
// End of readme  
// ============================================================  

